510—535: do not be misled by false analogies to think that the lapis molaris is not one uniform substance: it is as much so as copper, which you know to be copper after it is fused as well as before: other stones may burn 3 yet they never fuse like the molaria—One is tempted to think the main purpose of his poem was to enlighten the world on the true nature of the lapis molaris, which sciolists had grossly misre- presented.
